cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about fine-grained visual categorization, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper proposes a distance metric learning approach to address the challenges in FGVC, which involves learning an embedding to pull together data points from the same class and push apart those from different classes. This approach involves optimization, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a multi-stage metric learning framework to deal with high-dimensional feature vectors, which could also place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The paper also uses benchmark datasets to evaluate the proposed method, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of intra-class variation, which could also place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category.
